<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>DDB0126</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:14pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt; font-weight:bold">The Share Foundation – Written evidence</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Section 41, Draft De-regulation Bill &amp; Child Trust Fund Act 2004</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.7pt; padding-left:2.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">The purpose of Section 41 of the draft Bill is to provide flexibility for the administration of what are currently Child Trust Funds held for Looked After children, with specific reference to those whose registered contact is the Official Solicitor (or, in Scotland, the Accountant of Court). It therefore needs to be read in conjunction with the Child Trust Fund (CTF) - Junior ISA voluntary transfer proposals published by HM Treasury in May 2013, whose consultation period ended on 6 August. This would enable a registered contact for a CTF to give instructions for the transfer of that CTF to a Junior ISA. </span><br /><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></li><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.7pt; padding-left:2.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">CTFs were only issued for children born between 1 September 2002 and 2 January 2011. All other children are eligible to have Junior ISAs. In Budget 2011 the Chancellor announced that all Looked After children continuously in care for at least one year and who do not have a CTF would have a Junior ISA opened for them with an initial Government contribution of £200. The Share Foundation was appointed by the Department for Education in February 2012 to establish and administer these Junior ISA accounts, and has so far opened nearly 40,000 on the basis of data submitted by UK Local Authorities, including all Local Authorities in England and Wales.</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></li><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.7pt; padding-left:2.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">The Share Foundation’s role is to seek additional voluntary contributions to boost the value of the accounts and to provide financial education to prepare young people for adult life when they leave care. For more information please visit </span><a href="http://www.sharefound.org"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">www.sharefound.org</span></a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">, which provides detail on our activities appropriate for young people, their </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">carers</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">, Local Authorities, Junior ISA providers and donors respectively. </span><br /><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></li><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.7pt; padding-left:2.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">The new Junior ISA scheme applies to all eligible children in care: however the CTF arrangements for children in care drew a distinction between those with no </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">one</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> in a position of parental responsibility, where the registered contact is the Official Solicitor (or, in Scotland, the Accountant of Court) and those where there was someone in a position of parental responsibility when the account was opened. In the latter case that person administers the CTF as registered contact: in the former, the Official Solicitor (or, in Scotland, the Accountant of Court) carries out the administration.</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></li><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.7pt; padding-left:2.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Our response to the HM Treasury consultation on CTF - Junior ISA voluntary transfer is attached hereto, and you will note that The Share Foundation is hoping that the Government will decide to align the administration of</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> the</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> CTFs being administered by the Official Solicitor (or, in Scotland, the Accountant of Court) by transferring them into Junior ISAs for administration by The Share </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Foundation.</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></li><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.7pt; padding-left:2.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">This will have the advantages of:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">a.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">reducing the overall cost of administration to HM Government; </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">b.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">enabling additional voluntary contributions to be made </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">for</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> accounts previously held as C</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">TFs</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> a</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">long</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">ide</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">the more recently opened J</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">unior </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">ISAs;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">c.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">enabling</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> the young people </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">who previously had CTFs</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">(</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">the eldest of whom is no</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">w</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> 11 </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">years old) </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">to have access to the financial education materials available to those </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">with J</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">unior </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">ISA</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> </span><br /><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.7pt; padding-left:2.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">The Section 41 proposals in the Draft De-regulation Bill appear to provide the basis for such a transfer of these CTFs administered by the Official Solicitor (or, in Scotland, the Accountant of Court): although you should note that we have been unable to take legal advice as this is a very specialist area, and we do not have experience ourselves in analysing draft Government legislation. We presume that sufficient authority already exists for the Official Solicitor (or, in Scotland, the Accountant of Court) or the Secretary of State to instruct the transfer from the CTFs to Junior ISAs if this is permitted by HM Treasury, since they would need to be received as Junior ISAs.</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></li><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.7pt; padding-left:2.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">The proposals make no provision for CTFs whose registered contact is another person who has a position of parental responsibility for the Looked </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">After</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> child (i.e. those that are not administered by the Official Solicitor (or, in Scotland, the Accountant of Court). Any transfer to a Junior ISA to be administered by The Share Foundation could be instructed by such a person, although it is not easy to envisage how such a person could be located: the records would all be held by individual Local Authorities in arrangements dating back to 2005. However if they were so transferred The Share Foundation would be able to include them in the distribution of additional voluntary contributions, alongside the other accounts we administer.</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></li><li style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 15.7pt; padding-left:2.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Tra</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">nsfer to Junior ISA status would avoid other potential CTF problems, such as incompatibility of systems. It is a straightforward way to align provisions for young people in care which will otherwise continue to give rise to confusion for both Local Authorities and carers. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Please let us know if we can assist further on this matter: we would be pleased to attend the revision committee’s deliberations and provide additional information if required.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Gavin Oldham</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">The Share Foundation</span><br /><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">16 September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Attachment</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">:</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">to</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline"> The Share Foundation</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Unicode MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">’</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">s response to Section 41, Draft De-regulation Bill</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The Share Foundation</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Unicode MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">’</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">s Response to HM Treasury</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Unicode MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">’</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">s</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> Child Trust Fund - Junior ISA Consultation</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Thank you for the opportunity to respond to the above consultation. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">The Share Foundation is the Registered Contact for, and appointed operator of, the Junior ISA scheme for Looked After children, which was launched by the Department for Education in 2012. Over the past eight months we have opened c. 35,000 Junior ISAs on the basis of data provided by every Local Authority in England and Wales, 60% of Northern Irish health trusts, and 22% of Scottish Local Authorities. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Prior to our appointment we were in discussions with HM Treasury following our proposal to take over the administration and Registered Contact role for the Child Trust Funds administered by the Official Solicitor for Looked After children without anyone in a position of parental responsibility. We had made additional voluntary contributions to these accounts over the preceding five years. We put these discussions </span><span style="font-family:'Arial Unicode MS'; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">on hold</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Unicode MS'; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Unicode MS'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">during the early stages of implementing the Junior ISA scheme, but are now ready to re-open them.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">General Comments</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">There is a strong logic for bringing together the administration, financial education and voluntary fundraising roles to encompass all accounts held on behalf of Looked After children. Not only would there be economies of scale in relieving the Official Solicitor of this work, but also: </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">1. The financial education resources we have developed for Junior ISA recipients would be more widely available; and </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">2. We would be able to include accounts previously held as Child Trust Funds as beneficiaries of both unrestricted and geographically restricted voluntary fund-raising.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">We see the proposed voluntary transfer of Child Trust Funds to Junior ISAs as a significant opportunity to achieve the integration of administration of these accounts for Looked After children and young people. Since the Registered Contact for the Child Trust Funds is the Official Solicitor, and since all such accounts are held for children under the age of 16, a decision could be made to voluntarily transfer all such Child Trust Funds into Junior ISAs administered by The Share Foundation.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">There is, of course, a second category of Child Trust Funds for Looked After children </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">with</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt"> someone in a position of parental responsibility. These could of course remain where they are, but The Share Foundation would be happy to offer voluntary Junior ISA transfer facilities for these too: in which case they would also benefit from inclusion for allocation arising from our voluntary fund-raising </span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">programme</span><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Specific Questions</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Turning to the questions posed in the consultation document: </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">1. Yes, the transfer of funds from a Child Trust Fund to a Junior ISA should be permitted;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">2. We do not envisage any significant impact upon the viability of the wider Child Trust Fund market, provided that a number of simple alignment provisions are made to CTF regulations: including the removal of life-styling and the rollover into adult ISAs at age 18;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">3.  The approach will provide a workable basis for the transfer of funds from Child Trust Funds into Junior ISAs; </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">4. The Share Foundation will need to consider relatively minor changes to its system in order to be able to accommodate accounts transferred from the Official Solicitor: considerably less than would be needed to accommodate CTF administration. However we anticipate that the overall cost to Government will reduce significantly. Meanwhile the cost of charges to account holders would not change significantly as a result of the transfer; </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">5. We concur that voluntary transfer of Child Trust Funds to Junior ISAs, which in the case of accounts held for Looked After children will be driven by the Official Solicitor as Registered Contact, is the best course of action; </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">6. There would need to be much greater alignment between Child Trust Funds and Junior ISAs before a full merger could be considered; </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">7. We agree with the step-by-step approach set out in Sections 3.12 to 3.13 of the consultation document. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Gavin Oldham </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">Chair of Trustees </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">The Share Foundation</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Trebuchet MS'; font-size:12pt">25 July 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 70.9pt; text-indent:-70.9pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>